Sentencas: CuCo2O4 spinel nanopowders were synthesized by sol-gel method.
Titulo: Characterization of nanocrystalline CuCo2O4 spinel prepared by sol-gel technique applicable to the SOFC interconnect coating

Sentencas: The optimal values of pH and molar ratio of citric acid to metal ions (RC), and the influence of the calcination temperature and time were investigated.
Titulo: Characterization of nanocrystalline CuCo2O4 spinel prepared by sol-gel technique applicable to the SOFC interconnect coating

Sentencas: As-prepared materials were characterized by XRD, TGA, DSC, FE-SEM and electrical and coefficient of thermal expansion (CTE) measurements.
Titulo: Characterization of nanocrystalline CuCo2O4 spinel prepared by sol-gel technique applicable to the SOFC interconnect coating

Sentencas: It was found that pH = 4.5 and RC = 1 are the optimum conditions to produce pure CuCo2O4 nanopowders.
Titulo: Characterization of nanocrystalline CuCo2O4 spinel prepared by sol-gel technique applicable to the SOFC interconnect coating

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity was increased remarkably from 15.2 to 27.5 S cm(-1) with an increase in temperature from 500 to 800 A degrees C.
Titulo: Characterization of nanocrystalline CuCo2O4 spinel prepared by sol-gel technique applicable to the SOFC interconnect coating

Sentencas: Over the temperature range of 25-800 A degrees C, the CTE of CuCo2O4 was 11.4 x 10(-6) K-1 which is very close to the CTE of ferritic stainless steel (similar to 12 x 10(-6) K-1) used as solid oxide fuel cell interconnect.
Titulo: Characterization of nanocrystalline CuCo2O4 spinel prepared by sol-gel technique applicable to the SOFC interconnect coating
